"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-akani-simbine-blasts-team-south-africa-into-4x100m-relay-final-breaking-news-result\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbAkani Simbine blasts Team SA into 4x100m relay final  The South African men's 4x100m relay team qualified for the final after a blistering final leg in qualifying by Akani Simbine on Thursday.  The South African men's 4x100m relay team qualified for the final after a blistering final leg in qualifying byAkani Simbineon Thursday.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  Drawn in the first of two heats, the South African quartet were close to last when Simbine took the baton.  However, South Africa's star 100m runner blasted down the finishing straight to cross the line in second place behind the USA.  The top three finishers in each heat, plus the next two fastest times, qualified for the final.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  When all was said and done, South Africa wound up with the second-fastest overall time of37.94, giving them a real shot a medal in the final.  The South African team comprised Bayanda Walaza , Shaun Maswangani, Bradley Nkoana and Akani Simbine.  The USA posted the quickest time of37.47.  Joining the USA and South Africa in the final will be Great Britain, China, France, Canada, Japan and Italy.  Jamaica sensationally missed out on a place in the final.  The final will be held onFriday, 9 Augustat19:47(SA time).  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"